name: Lakers
summary: The Denver Nuggets and Los Angeles Lakers are set to face off in the first round of the NBA playoffs. The Nuggets, who finished the regular season with the sixth seed in the Western Conference, will host the Lakers, who finished as the seventh seed. The two teams met in the first round of the playoffs last year, with the Nuggets winning in five games. LeBron James' triple-double helped the Lakers beat the Pelicans and advance to face the Nuggets in a play-in rematch. The Lakers survived a Pelicans' rally to punch their NBA Playoffs ticket. The Nuggets worked over the Lakers to pick up where they left off from last year. Fans can listen live to the game on SiriusXM Blog and watch it on NBA.com. Key questions for the series include how the Lakers will handle the altitude in Denver and the Nuggets' strong defense.

The bill now moves to the Senate, where it faces an uncertain future. The Biden administration has also expressed concerns about TikTok, citing national security risks. TikTok has denied these allegations, and says it does not share user data with the Chinese government. name: John Sterling
summary: Legendary Yankees radio broadcaster John Sterling has announced his retirement after 36 seasons and 5,631 games behind the microphone. Sterling, known for his enthusiastic and distinctive style, has been a beloved figure in the Yankees organization and among fans. His iconic home run call, "It is high, it is far, it is gone," has become synonymous with Yankees baseball. Sterling's retirement marks the end of an era, having provided the soundtrack to countless Yankees victories and memorable moments. He leaves with a legacy of exceptional broadcasting and a lasting impact on the sport.

name: Cybertruck recall
summary: Tesla has issued a massive recall of 3,878 Cybertrucks due to a faulty accelerator pedal. The recall, which is the largest in the company's history, affects all Cybertrucks produced to date. The issue stems from a soapy substance that can accumulate on the pedal, causing it to stick in the depressed position. This could lead to unintended acceleration and increase the risk of a crash. The recall marks the latest setback for Tesla, which has faced a series of production delays and technical issues with the Cybertruck. The recall comes at a particularly difficult time for Elon Musk, the company's CEO, who is also embroiled in a legal battle over his acquisition of Twitter.
